title: Ashley DeBauge advances to Day 2 of state
text:
Laura Schwinn/Special to the Gazette Special to the Gazette 
Emporia High’s Ashley DeBauge returns a volley Friday at the 5A state tennis meet in Valley Center. Laura Schwinn/Special to the Gazette Kathryn Kienholz, Chelsea Herrarte 
Emporia High’s Kathryn Kienholz, back, serves in a doubles match with partner Chelsea Herrarte, front, Friday in Valley Center. Laura Schwinn/Special to the Gazette Kathryn Kienholz, Chelsea Herrarte Laura Schwinn/Special to the Gazette Kathryn Kienholz, Chelsea Herrarte Ashley DeBauge advances to Day 2 of state The Emporia Gazette emporiagazette.com | 0 comments 
Emporia High’s Ashley DeBauge advanced to day two of the 5A state tennis tournament in Valley Center, while the Spartans’ doubles team of Chelsea Herrarte and Kathryn Kienholz saw their season end with two losses in a field of tough competition. 
DeBauge cruised past her first round opponent, Valley Center’s Carly Espinosa, with a 6-0, 6-0 victory. The Spartan senior then took down Colby Mortenson from Lansing, 6-0, 6-1, to advance to the quarterfinals. 
DeBauge lost her final match of the day to Bishop Carroll’s Natalie Lubbers, 6-3, 7-5, and will play in the fifth-place bracket Saturday.
